h2-h4-h5} (19. Qd2 Nxd4 20. Bxd4 Rc6 21. f4 Bxd4+ 22. Qxd4 Rf7 23. Qd3 Qc8 24.
h3 Qf8 25. Qg3 Rc2 26. a3 Qc8 27. Kh2 Rc3 28. Rd3 Rxd3 29. Qxd3 Qf8 30. g3 Rc7
31. h4 d5 32. exd5 Qd6 {1/2-1/2 (75) Kryvoruchko,Y (2692) -Yilmaz,M (2633)
Heraklio 2017}) 19... Nxd4 20. Bxd4 Bxd4 21. Rxd4 Rc6 22. Rfd1 Rfc8 23. h4 {
[%cal Gd1d2,Gf2g3,Gh4h5] I treat this position as somewhat uncomfortable for
Black, albeit White has nothing real (yet). There's some serious pressure on
