Rad1 Rc6 24. R1d2 f6 25. Na4 Kf7 26. Nb6 Rd8 27. b3 $14)) 4... a6 {a very
logical order of the moves - now White has to either take on d7 or retreat to
d3 or e2, since the c4 square comes under a tempo of b7-b5 and a4 is simply
impossible. If Black will postpone playing ... a6, after White's Re1 it will
give a yet another appealing retreat option - f1 square.} (4... Ngf6 {this
